ent.origin: Late Middle English (in the sense 'free from (a liability')): from Latin immunis 'exempt from public service or charge', from in- 'not' + munis 'ready for service'. Senses relating to physiological resistance date from the late 19th century.

p.def: squeeze or pack tightly into a specified space.
p.eg: Four of us were jammed in one compartment.

p.def: an instance of a thing seizing or becoming stuck.
p.eg: You can then sprinkle the petit suisse with sugar or strawberry jam.
